heir cultural visibility and agency. What this study foregrounds is how women characters succeed in making themselves heard even if their voices are silenced in the end.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAmerican fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen entertainerszGreat Britain. 0aWomen entertainerszUnited States. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aVoice.  agender.  along nineteenth century.  anarrative fiction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishz978311060418408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2018z9783110603187oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105586610 cprintz978311055842540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311056104340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110561043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110561043/original  a978-3-11-060418-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-